I"ð1<p>Many bioinformaticians/ computational biologists will make a common mistake once or twice in their career. One such is to mix reference files. For eg. reference fill will have chromosomes denoted by numbers (1,2,3 etc), and vcf file is denoted by alphanumeric string (chr1, chr2, chr3 etc). To add to this, each bioinformaticis server has itâ€™s own formatting for reference files. Let us take NCBI for today. I have downloaded recent GRCh38 assembly from <a href="https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/refseq/H_sapiens/annotation/GRCh38_latest/refseq_identifiers/">here</a>. Headers of the sequences in file is  a long list and few of them are as follows.</p>

